  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "Credibility assessment for CFD-based hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) operating conditions. The bound requirement specifies that the computational model must predict absolute hemolysis index (HI) within ±15% of in-vitro measurements across the VAD operating envelope (2000–3500 RPM, 4–8 L/min flow). Model Risk Level 5 applies given Class III device classification and direct use of predicted HI in regulatory submission. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification covers inlet flow rate, fluid viscosity, and pump rotational speed. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are addressed; 7 are formally assessed and 6 are scoped to epistemic gap documentation. The overall credibility determination is Accepted conditional on the documented gap-closure plan being executed prior to PMA submission.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-hi-prediction-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-cfd-hemolysis-within-15pct-tolerance",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-generic-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-invitro-hemolysis-benchmark",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/vad-operating-envelope-boundary-conditions",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/monte-carlo-uq-samples-n10000"
  ],
